<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ambitious" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ambitious,</orth> desirous of superiority, of honor and power: <bibl n="shak. luc 150" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 150</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.152" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 1, 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 4, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.4.114" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.2.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 2, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.112" default="NO" valid="yes">3, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.182" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 182</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.132" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 132</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.264" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 264</bibl> etc. Placed after its subst.: <cit><quote>love a.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.430" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 430</bibl></cit>. Followed by <emph>for</emph>: <cit><quote>I am a. for a motley coat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ayl 2.7.43" default="NO" valid="yes">As II, 7, 43</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you are a. for poor knaves' caps,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 76</bibl></cit>.
